  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6828 sitting just below the max positive gamma wall at 6830 (131.8B), dealers are actively selling into this rally and providing strong resistance at current levels. The PIN regime confirms dealers are long gamma and stabilizing price action, with the immediate downside supported by massive positive gamma walls at 6825 (77.4B) and 6820 (63.7B) where dealers will buy any dips. Key levels to watch are the 6830 resistance where dealer selling intensifies and the GEX flip at 6787 - any break below turns dealers short gamma and removes the stabilizing bid.\n\n**Bottom line:** Expect the market to get pinned between 6820-6830 with limited downside given the massive gamma support walls.",
